10:T40c,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Person","name":"Mithun Chakraborty","image":"https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/4z8c5YAe0TCkEZNHXWlKxNTD8sV.jpg","description":"Mithun Chakraborty is an Indian actor, film producer and entrepreneur and politician. In a career spanning over five decades, he has done 350 films, mostly in Hindi and Bengali languages, and a few in Odia, Telugu, Tamil, Kannada, and Punjabi. Referred to as \"Mahaguru\", he is a former Rajya Sabha Member of Parliament. He is the recipient of three National Film Awards and four Filmfare Awards. In January 2024, Chakraborty was awarded the Padma Bhushan, the third-highest civilian honour by the Government of India. He was also awarded India's highest accolade in the field of cinema, the Dadasaheb Phalke Award for the year 2022, whose announcement came from the Union Ministry of Information and Broadcasting in September 2024.","jobTitle":"Acting","url":"https://gdvg-ten.vercel.app/people/576702/mithun-chakraborty","sameAs":["https://imdb.com/name/nm0149822"]}5:[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$10"}}],["$","$L11",null,{"person":{"id":"2321c4b5-92eb-4362-9000-24171c2d32f0","tmdb_id":85450,"name":"Mithun Chakraborty","gender":2,"biography":"Mithun Chakraborty is an Indian actor, film producer and entrepreneur and politician. In a career spanning over five decades, he has done 350 films, mostly in Hindi and Bengali languages, and a few in Odia, Telugu, Tamil, Kannada, and Punjabi. Referred to as \"Mahaguru\", he is a former Rajya Sabha Member of Parliament. He is the recipient of three National Film Awards and four Filmfare Awards. In January 2024, Chakraborty was awarded the Padma Bhushan, the third-highest civilian honour by the Government of India. He was also awarded India's highest accolade in the field of cinema, the Dadasaheb Phalke Award for the year 2022, whose announcement came from the Union Ministry of Information and Broadcasting in S